<p>On the MS Azure platform I see that it's possible to get Usage data with the following API call: </p>  <pre><code>https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/ {subscription-id}/providers/Microsoft.Commerce/ UsageAggregates?api-version=2015-06-01-preview&amp; reportedStartTime=2013-02-01T00%3A00%3A00&amp; reportedEndTime=2015-02-08T00%3A00%3A00&amp; aggregationGranularity=Daily&amp; showDetails=false </code></pre>  <p>Which gets you things like 'Compute Hours' usage data but I can't find a way to get utilisation metrics {CPU, disk io, etc}</p>  <p>It seems like it should be possible as the 'metricDefinitions' API lists these operations as available for a resource:</p>  <pre><code>https://management.azure.com/subscriptions/ {subscription-id}/resourceGroups/ {resource-grp-name}/providers/Microsoft.ClassicCompute/virtualMachines/ {resource-name}/metricDefinitions? api-version=2014-04-01&amp; </code></pre>  <p>but I see no Rest endpoint for 'metrics' on a given resource.</p>  <p>Any help much appreciated!</p>